President Joe Biden met with Members of Congress and Transportation Secretary Pete Buttigieg to discuss the importance of the investments outlined in the American Jobs Plan. The bipartisan group of Members of Congress, who are former governors and mayors, have firsthand experience with the need for federal investment in infrastructure. The President and Secretary Buttigieg shared their vision for creating jobs, rebuilding infrastructure, and ensuring the United States can compete with China. The meeting included discussions on specific components of the plan and how to fund them. President Biden emphasized the need for action and asked for feedback and follow-up from the Members of Congress. This meeting is part of the Administration's efforts to engage with Congress and stakeholders on the American Jobs Plan.